transforma.qb2_user_app.rosmsg

Class InspectionResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • transforma.qb2_user_app.rosmsg.InspectionResult
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RosBridgeListener

    public class InspectionResult
extends java.lang.Object
implements RosBridgeListener
  • This is a singleton class of inspection result that only creates itself when the inspection starts
  • It's created to store relevant numbers relating to inspection result.
  • Check whether the inspectionMode result attribute is null or not to determine whether there is an ongoing inspection.
  • Making inspectionResult null pointer is necessary when an inspection finishes.
  • Adding & Removing RosBridgeListener is necessary to prevent error occuring

      • onMessage

        public void onMessage(java.lang.String message,
                      RosMsgRaw rosMsgRaw)
        This method is a large onMessage method basically to update and display inspection information onto the screen Case by case review is necessary Note: For case pointCloud, parsing is not done by loading entire string into memory to form large class objects as it generate tens of thousands, of RosTopicMessage_MsgGeometry_Point object which would crash the java heap size and may lead to GC of other critical class objects such as RosBridgeConnection Paring is done using jsonReader which implements streamReader. This helps to maintain a low memory usage. Note that for other large data blocks, such method should also be used
        Specified by:
        onMessage in interface RosBridgeListener
        Parameters:
        message - Raw message string
        rosMsgRaw - rawMessage object with op field

                              throws java.io.IOException,

        THis method reads the points field of the RosMessage for pointCloud data and converts it into a float[]
